try colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Schematic overview 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Real example 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-678CB99E-0B0F-4B76-A1C0-56419AFB3DE8" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2CB47942-E3DE-4F6A-814E-11BB8B9FFE6E-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2CB47942-E3DE-4F6A-814E-11BB8B9FFE6E-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-6C1B96F1-6309-4899-AFE3-420272DAED23" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-7427C439-3D1B-45AC-83C9-CFA3964CB8D2-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7427C439-3D1B-45AC-83C9-CFA3964CB8D2-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-EC1EAE23-40EC-4B10-A2C9-83873F76DC70" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Collect</title><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Symptoms</b> 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Discrete darker and lighter bands. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Width of lighter/darker band is 12 mm.
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Width of darker/lighter band is 39 mm.
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Lower OD (optical density) than expected.
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Functional logging (if available)</b>
</p><p class="- topic/p ">No logging available which can pinpoint to this case.
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ADAM-triggers</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">No ADAM-triggers available. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-DDCC1BB0-B402-4010-9156-67DB737F3DE5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Analyze/Repair</title><p class="- topic/p ">If these bands are still visible after 1 meter of printing the media is not suitable for the Colorado family. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If the level of banding after 1 meter is sufficient, there are two options:
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Feed 1 meter of media before starting a new print
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Use the locked tension bar in the profile.
</p></li></ol></section><section id="GUID-2513E5DF-C282-453D-9841-6E539DB0EB51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluate/Prevention</title></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">X-tran rollers are pressing against the media. The top layer of some soft media is sensitive to this pressure. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When printing from the leading edge, the media is retracted to determine its width and leading edge. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This means the x-tran rollers are pressing twice or three times over the same spot. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">By using a locked tension bar this part of the media cannot be used for printing and the visibly should degrees. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Another option is cutting the first meter of media. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-E296D1A5-6E40-45FA-8995-87FBE4000791.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
